    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Events can be used to allow external code to respond to state changes in an object. There are roughly 3 types of event declarations:</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Auto events, where the compiler sets up the mechanism behind the event</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Single line declarations, with a simple ADD expression(list) and REMOVE expression(list).</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">Multi line declarations with a separate ADD block and/or REMOVE block</text></li>
    </list>
